CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782902882
OL,3,CPatient tests negative for Ebola after
OL,4,Csuspected case at Glasgow hospital
OL,6,FThere have been almost 700 confirmed
OL,7,Fcases of bundibugyo Ebola virus, the
OL,8,Fmajority of which are in the
OL,9,FDemocratic Republic of Congo. Some 138
OL,10,Fpeople have died, including two in
OL,11,Fneighbouring Uganda.
OL,13,FIf confirmed, it would have been the
OL,14,Ffirst case in the UK since the
OL,15,Foutbreak in the DRC was declared a
OL,16,Fpublic health emergency of
OL,17,Finternational concern by the World
OL,18,FHealth Organisation (WHO).
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
